      "description": "This 996.2 Carrera is powered by the 3.6L flat-six engine featuring VarioCam Plus for optimized valve timing and lift. The power is delivered through a G96 6-speed manual transaxle, offering precise shift throws and a direct mechanical connection. The chassis dynamics are defined by a well-sorted multi-link rear suspension and MacPherson struts up front, providing excellent lateral grip and communicative steering feedback. Proactive maintenance has been performed, including an IMS bearing retrofit and rear main seal replacement, ensuring the longevity of the M96 architecture. The braking system retains its original four-piston monobloc calipers, providing firm pedal feel and consistent deceleration. While the exterior shows minor road patina, the drivetrain remains tight with sharp throttle response and a clean induction note.",
